data.title: Visits by Foreign Leaders
data.text: President Milan Kucan Attended dedication of the Holocaust Memorial Museum and met with President Clinton on April 21. April 20–22, 1993 Prime Minister Janez Drnovsek Met with President Clinton at the UN General Assembly in New York City. October 22, 1995 Prime Minister Janez Drnovsek Working visit. Afterwards visited Cleveland, Ohio. November 2–5, 1998 Prime Minister Janez Drnovsek Attended NATO’s 50th Anniversary Summit. April 23–25, 1999 Prime Minister Janez Drnovsek Working visit. May 13–17, 2002 Prime Minister Anton Rop Working visit. Attended NATO Accession ceremony. March 28–30, 2004 Prime Minister Janez Jansa Working visit. July 7–11, 2006 Prime Minister Borut Pahor Working visit. February 9, 2011
